name: 1h-carbazole, 2,3,4,9-tetrahydro-

The introduction of the carbazole ring introduces a rigid structure with increased molecular weight, which raises the melting point. The methoxy group introduces additional hydrogen bonding potential, which can further lower the melting point. The carbazole ring itself can participate in hydrogen bonding, which may raise the melting point by approximately +10°C. The methoxy group can also increase the melting point due to the increased molecular weight and van der Waals forces, estimated at around +5°C. The presence of a nitro group can also contribute to the melting point due to its ability to participate in hydrogen bonding and increase molecular weight, estimated at around +5°C.
